{
  "texts": [
    "I intend the comparison point of 100 million human deaths to refer to deaths which happen against the will of the people dying and happening to people who would otherwise have had average human lives.",
    "For the purposes of this paper, I take for granted that 100 million human deaths of such kind are very bad.",
    "Furthermore, some people may argue that even small effects (e.g., a minor worsening of human values) can be catastrophic if they persist so as to affect humanities whole future [6][7][8].",
    "To constrain the scope of this paper, I do not count these cases as catastrophic here.",
    "2 According to Sparrow [9], superintelligent AI would -even if it behaves in accordance with human interests -undermine human freedom since it has power over humans."
  ]
}